          "description": "I wouldn\u2019t recommend going here. They want you in and out as fast as possible, I didn\u2019t feel like they cared about me at all. I had an allergy test done and the tech who saw me literally had a kitchen timer and reset it every time he spoke to a new patient. A kitchen timer. He didn\u2019t even try to hide it. He pricked me with the allergy test and then put me in a busy hallway to wait. The reception area is a den of chaos the likes of which I\u2019ve never seen. Josh Safdie levels of stress. I was holding my coat and purse and the girl at reception would. Not. Stop. Handing me paper after paper after paper and clipboards and telling me to scan QR codes even after I asked her twice to slow down. They also forgot my bloodwork.\n\nThe nurses and receptionists seem very nice and were helpful and I could tell they care a lot and  work really hard in a really challenging environment. It\u2019s too much going on in too small of a space.",
