          "description": "Your review:\nI have no issue with my primary care doctor and the rest of staff over at 912 Columbus Ave. However, I do have an issue with the Allery Doctor who was very rude and he had a nasty attitude, he was quick to rush me off. He didn't care about my concerns and was quick to give me a wrong evaluation saying I got asthma?? When I'm walking perfectly fine with out huffing and puffing and not losing my breath. He prescribed me a asthma spray?? which I refused to take! And they got to stop rushing me out of there! Also, my primary care referred me to a sleep apnea test, they won't take my insurance. Other issue is that I had a sonogram which required a follow-up appointment which I tried with front desk. They are now saying I can't to a follow-up because they won't take my insurance! You just did a test on me and took my insurance! Now you don't take my insurance! Very confusing and disappointed experience! What the hell is going in this facility! Also, I noticed a lot of people coming in here. It could be crowded at times which I don't like. It's a mixed bunch at front desk. You got some nice ones and you got some with attitude problems like when I called about my follow-up for gastroenterologist, the girl had a nasty attitude and was quick to say we don't accept your insurance and hung up on my face! Really classy! Trained your staff better! This is a medical office and not the projects!\n\nClick a review site below:\n\nPowered by Lauer Media Company",
