          "description": "I gave this medical office a chance to do better.. I appreciate the testing that they provided and their online portal, but I am done with them.  Reaching a human is not easy, especially when you want to speak to a staff from a different office. At the beginning directions for certain testing was not discussed, and led to rescheduling appointments which it frowned upon but it was not my fault.  It took a follow up appointment a month later to find out the pharmacy they sent to never contacted me and now with my pharmacy its been 2 weeks for an authorization but you get the run around and blame the pharmacy. again 2 weeks and no reply.  The bedside manner of the mri tech was not pleasant except for one who I submitted a positive feedback about is Richard at 14th street, he explains every question.  A few times waiting time was bad, but I understand things can get hectic but an hour and half for neurology appointment in the Columbus office was very frustrating.  The columbus office staff are overall pleasant, the checkout process should be more clear, if not you wind up sitting and waiting.  I believe they finally fixed the check in process, meaning I would check in on my phone and then again when I arrive scan code and answer same questions, not too sure, my last appointment I didnt need to do double check in on the app and barcode.  A patient should not have to be on top of staff to do their job, especially when one is dealing with medical concerns, the last thing one needs is lack of communication, and compassion.  An admin that was really helpful I believe his name is Felix, turns out he is no longer with them.  I truly wish to find doctors who listen like Dr Rachunow, I was glad to have met her and have a positive experience.",
