          "description": "I\u2019m not the type of person who leaves bad reviews but what happened to me at Medical Arts, and I\u2019m sure with other patients as well, needs to be looked at.\nI was diagnosed with disc herniation and stenosis. Had an appointment yesterday at 3:40pm with a pain management doctor, and with a spine specialist today at 10am, both appointments scheduled over 2 weeks ago.\nI arrived early for my 3:40 and while was waiting to check in, got a call from Medical Arts canceling my 10am today because the doctor would not be in office. Had to reschedule for May 19th.\nWaited until 4:30 to be called in for my 3:40 appointment (I was told at the front desk that the doctor likes to take her time with the patients) to hear that yesterday was the doctor\u2019s first day at Medical Arts and she is not yet credentialed so she couldn\u2019t give ANY SORT of treatment or prescribe anything. No injections, no medicine, no physical therapy. Nothing. According to her, she was told by the owner, that same morning, that her credential would be ready in 6 MONTHS and she couldn\u2019t practice but she could offer injections for a few hundred dollars, but she didn\u2019t feel comfortable doing that.\nI was in absolute shock listening to all of that. Medical Arts made me wait 2 weeks plus the hour I waited at the hall, in excruciating pain on my lower back and both legs to hear I couldn\u2019t get any treatment because the doctor isn\u2019t credentialed yet and the other doctor that could do it wasn\u2019t working and they had no idea when he would come back.\nI\u2019ve been taking anti inflammatories for over a month just to be able to function (even though I\u2019m not supposed to due to the side effects), risking my kidneys and liver, and left the practice with no direction, no treatment, nothing. Just the biggest waste of time of my life and a feeling that what I\u2019m going through, and other people too, don\u2019t matter. It depends on a credential or a few hundred dollars.\nI called Medical Arts after I left the facility  and asked why they let me wait all this time, untreated, in pain, to hear what I heard and they told me that by doing what they did I was able to at least see a pain doctor. For what??? To have a chat about the weather?\nThis whole situation was unbelievably unprofessional, I am now left still in pain plus with this feeling that we, the patients, really don\u2019t matter. I\u2019m sure my insurance was billed for this \u201cappointment\u201d and I lost a day (meaning payment) at work because of what they did to me. Who will be held responsible for this? If I miss my appointment with them I have to pay a fee. What about what I missed? And everything I am going through?\nIf you are a patient going to see a pain management or spine specialist, call them and cancel so you don\u2019t have to go through what I went through. If I had known what was going on before, I could\u2019ve booked another appointment to have my problem looked at at least 2 weeks ago and probably wouldn\u2019t be taking the pills I\u2019m taking and would not be in pain anymore.\nI wrote them messages through the patient portal, emailed de patient care supervisor and am waiting for an answer. Let\u2019s just have this registered here too.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tSTVJuRXpVbEpOVlVVMFFrdEVUbXMwZUVOWE0yYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa32bfe6c5e398b3f!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkRMRnEzUlJNVUU0QktETms0eENXM2c%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "a month ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-05-06T12:06:19+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Paul Stetzer",
          "rating": 4,
          "contributor_id": "111570009153782233633",
          "user_review_count": 2,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBb8YV6iFouSzOeUH04XIRvstFRLz7lctU4euf70ObICRQSmA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "My appointment with Dr. Wilbur was great: she listens, she reflects, she asks good questions, she offers sound advice. I very much trust her. So, I would definitely recommend her.\n\nAll the back and forth and the form-completing before the actual visit are off-putting. It seems that much of the info already exists. And one reminder a few days before an appointment should;d suffice.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2tsamIzY3dXV1pmZUdacGJEUTBjMlJxWHpoQ2JHYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa32bfe6c5e398b3f!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOkljb3cwWWZfeGZpbDQ0c2RqXzhCbGc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "5 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-01-16T19:54:19+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Mr. Eejay",
          "rating": 3,
          "contributor_id": "101289033583766473225",
          "user_review_count": 8,
          "user_photo_count": 3,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKv5zSutNrK-n35z7L2vWCmQrMoUhlTQBlWEvUrPDOgq7yVRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "My doctor was amazing. I really liked her energy, and she made me feel very comfortable. That positive experience made me want to continue care with this doctor and this practice.\n\nUnfortunately, the billing experience was very disappointing. While I was signing the paperwork, I specifically asked whether I would be charged because the forms suggested I might be, and I usually am not charged. I made it clear that if I was going to be billed, I did not want to move forward. The staff checked my insurance and told me I would not be charged. However, I later received a bill anyway.\n\nBecause of that, I ended up canceling all of my appointments. It is very frustrating to be told one thing upfront and then be billed afterward.\n\nI also found the communication excessive. They send far too many emails and text messages, which felt overwhelming and unnecessary.\n\nBased on my experience, the doctor was excellent, but the billing and communication practices were not.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25aWlFWTnViWG8yU0ZadWJXOUtOV1psYzI1alZXYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xa32bfe6c5e398b3f!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOnZZQVNubXo2SFZubW9KNWZlc25jVWc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "2 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-04-20T14:10:29+00:00"
        }
      ]
